EmoLib: Emotional Library
=========================

EmoLib is a library that extracts the affect and emotions 
from an incoming text by tagging such text according to 
the feeling that is written or being conveyed.

EmoLib has been coded in the Java programming language.

----------

This README text file only provides a general description of
the project.

In order to obtain the project's files organisation please refer
to the HACKING text file included in the source code and
development distributions of EmoLib.

The information relating to the different modules that compose
EmoLib are pertinently documented in the Javadocs.
Please build the system first as indicated in the INSTALL file 
and launch a web browser with the "doc/index.html" file, or else visit
the [EmoLib online API](http://atrilla.net/data/files/emolibdoc/index.html).


----------

For any comment or suggestion of any kind, you may contact
